      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CONFIDENTIALITY (3) returns from a five-month break. Produced a strong set of figures at her second race start with a tough on-pace Maiden win over 1100m at Wyong. Has clearly come back well judging by the two trial placings. This looks a good launching pad. CHARKA (4) pulled out plenty when winning first-up over 1000m at Gosford. Bumped into a handy C1 field when raced flat to finish sixth over 1000m at Hawkesbury. Finds an easier race and is set to bounce back. CHARLINA (2) deep into the campaign and gets a better set-up for this from the inside draw. Gripped on late from the outside barrier with a game third over 1100m at Hawkesbury in BM64 grade. Claim helps again and sure to be thereabouts. TRUCE (8) progressive mare who returns for her second campaign. Fitted with the one 800m trial placing and look for her late from the wide gate.",
